==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bogue
<hw>Bogue</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>To fall off from the wind; to edge away to leeward; -- said only of
inferior craft.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bogue</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Bogue
<hw>Bogue</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The
boce; -- called also <altname>bogue bream</altname>. See
<er>Boce</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bogus</ent>⟦br⟧
